Step 1 – Start Installation

Start the FOSS-Cloud installer and select:

Single Server Installation

This installs all components on one machine.

Step 2 – Configure Network Interface

Check available interfaces:

ip addr

Select network interface such as:

eth0
Step 3 – Configure Domain and IP

Enter network details during installation:

Domain Name : foss-cloud.org
Static IP   : 192.168.1.100
Gateway     : 192.168.1.1
DNS         : 8.8.8.8

This sets the server network configuration.

Step 4 – Confirm Installation

The installer will install all required components including:

Virtual machine manager

Storage services

Network services

After installation, reboot the system.

Step 5 – Access Administrator Page

Open a web browser and enter:

http://192.168.1.100

Login credentials:

Username : admin
Password : admin

This opens the FOSS-Cloud dashboard.

Step 6 – Upload ISO File

Navigate in dashboard:

Virtual Machine → Upload ISO

Upload operating system image such as:

Ubuntu ISO
Windows ISO

This ISO will be used to create virtual machines.

Step 7 – Create VM Template

Configure the virtual machine template with parameters:

Template Name
Operating System Type
CPU Allocation
Memory Allocation
Disk Size
Network Interface

This template will be used to create new VMs.

Step 8 – Deploy Virtual Machine

Navigate:

VM Templates → Run

The system will start a new virtual machine.

The VM status changes to:

Running
Step 9 – Access Virtual Machine

To access the VM:

Download SPICE client tool

Click the connection link

Enter VM password

The VM desktop window will open.

Step 10 – Manage Virtual Resources

Administrator can perform the following tasks:

Create multiple virtual machines
Allocate storage
Configure networks
Monitor VM status
Stop or restart VMs
Output
FOSS-Cloud installed successfully
ISO image uploaded
VM template created
Virtual machine deployed and running